items.title: 'Peel-and-go' printable structures fold themselves
items.summary: Researchers have created a printable structure that begins to fold itself up as soon as it's peeled off the printing platform.

items.title: Squirrels use 'chunking' to organize their favorite nuts
items.summary: Like trick-or-treaters sorting their Halloween candy haul, fox squirrels apparently organize their stashes of nuts by variety, quality and possibly even preference, according to new research.

items.title: Climate change challenges the survival of fish across the world
items.summary: Researchers have published the first analysis looking at how vulnerable the world's freshwater and marine fishes are to climate change. Their study used physiological data to predict how nearly 3,000 fish species living in oceans and rivers will respond to warming water temperatures in different regions.
